JSTL Tag Library (JSP Standard Tag library)
	- It is collection of predefined tags to simply the jsp development
	- Advantages
		1 Fast Development JSTL provides many tags that simplify the JSP.
		2 Code Reusability We can use the JSTL tags on various pages.
		3 No need to use scriptlet tag It avoids the use of scriptlet tag.
	
	- Core Tag
		1 The JSTL core tag provide variable support, URL management, flow control, etc. The URL for the core tag is http://java.sun.com/jsp/jstl/core. The prefix of core tag is c.
		
		2 control struct: if, switch, loop, ...
		  manipulating variables
		  http related: redirect, url, ...
	
	- SQL Tag
		1 The JSTL SQL tags provide SQL support. The URL for the SQL tags is http://java.sun.com/jsp/jstl/sql and prefix is sql.
		2 invoke SQL queries from JSP pages -- encapsulate JDBC code
		3 not recommended -- no separation in view and backend layer
	- xml --> xml
		1 xml processing -- parsing, making, ...
	- fn --> functions
		1 simple string functions/String manipulation	

How to JSTL Steps as follow
- Using JSTL:
		step1: add jstl jar in classpath -- WEB-INF/lib.
		step2: in JSP page import it using <%@ taglib ... %>
			e.g. <%@taglib prefix="c" uri="..." %>
					<c:redirect url="..."/>		
		
		
		